<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-01T20:00:00-05:00" n="1137" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d1137">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi></head>
                            <p>From May 22–25 the Secretary of State was in Pakistan, as part of a
                                trip he made to the Middle East with the Director of Mutual
                                Security. For a complete set of the memoranda of conversation
                                between the Secretary and Pakistani officials, see <ref target="frus1952-54v09p1">volume IX</ref>.</p>
                        </div>
